metadata.reasoningText:
Now I understand the `isRead` logic:

```typescript
private isRead(session: IInternalAgentSessionData): boolean {
    if (this.isArchived(session)) {
        return true; // archived sessions are always read
    }

    const readDate = this.sessionStates.get(session.resource)?.read;

    return (readDate ?? AgentSessionsModel.READ_STATE_INITIAL_DATE) >= (session.timing.lastRequestEnded ?? session.timing.lastRequestStarted ?? session.timing.created);
}
```

The issue: Every chat interaction (sending a message) updates `session.timing.lastRequestStarted` and `session.timing.lastRequestEnded`. 

When these timestamps advance, the `isRead` check fails because the readDate was set earlier, so the session appears "unread" again even though the user is actively viewing it. The suggestion is to auto-mark a session as read when it's the currently focused one and receives new messages, rather than letting the timing updates flip it back to unread. I need to check how the system tracks which session is currently active.

